1
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:15,460
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

2
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,460
What happened? Didn't you go to Paris?

3
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:36,310
I am not going. And I have an idea for the first scene of that script.

4
00:00:36,310 --> 00:00:37,920
What's that?

5
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:50,680
Also, the first line is...

6
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:54,770
I like you.

7
00:00:57,670 --> 00:01:00,010
And the second line is...

8
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:07,440
♬ I love you which I practiced for countless days ♬

9
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:15,480
♬ Always you will be the the person who is the same as a spring day for me ♬

10
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:22,770
♬ I know you better than anyone in the world. ♬

11
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:32,700
♬ Now is the time I love you ... ♬

12
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,250
Episode 15

13
00:01:36,540 --> 00:01:38,110
Thank you.

14
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,610
What are you looking at?

15
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:55,220
Oh... I was just looking at people walking by.

16
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:02,250
Are you really going to Paris?

17
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:06,300
This is really disconcerting.

18
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:09,050
It's more disconcerting that you declined your transfer.

19
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:11,950
You were on a flight, so I couldn't tell you about my decision.

20
00:02:11,950 --> 00:02:15,530
I wanted to talk with you today, but what's this all of a sudden?

21
00:02:15,530 --> 00:02:18,620
I thought it would be really difficult for me if I didn't get to see you for a long time.

22
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:21,550
That's why I decided to go for three months.

23
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:24,010
You must go, right?

24
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:27,520
I really don't want to go. Since you are not going.

25
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:31,390
We are so funny.

26
00:02:31,390 --> 00:02:35,700
I ran over here to hold on to you since you're leaving.

27
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,900
I don't know what I should do next.

28
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:43,310
But we already confirmed our feelings for each other. That's enough.

29
00:02:51,850 --> 00:02:53,940
I will call you as soon as I land.

30
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:56,390
Sure, jerk.

31
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:57,340
What?

32
00:02:57,340 --> 00:03:00,070
Do you like it? Going away like this, jerk?

33
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:03,370
If you act like this, it makes me really sad.

34
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:14,800
Oh... This.

35
00:03:21,550 --> 00:03:26,100
Every time I change my bag, I always put this necklace in it.

36
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,460
I can't mix it with other things.

37
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:31,210
I see.

38
00:03:32,790 --> 00:03:34,310
Give it to me.

39
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,600
How is it?

40
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,950
I thought it would suit you well.

41
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:01,450
Come back safely.

42
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:17,450
Will we be able to make it?

43
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:18,860
Yes.

44
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:28,850
Even if we're apart or close, we're always together.

45
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:41,510
Won! Call me as soon as you arrive!

46
00:05:15,310 --> 00:05:16,670
Hello.
Two months later

47
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:18,400
Hello!

48
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,830
Good Morning!

49
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:32,210
I woke up so early. I am so tired.

50
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:49,160
Team Leader, we have a meeting in ten minutes.

51
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,550
Yes, I got it.

52
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,740
- Welcome!
- Yes.

53
00:05:57,740 --> 00:05:59,660
Have a seat.

54
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:07,960
Despite refusing your transfer, what's the reason the China case is personally looking for you?

55
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:13,540
They say sometimes, the more you want it, the more you have to let it go.

56
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,290
If it's really yours, it will come back to you without fail.

57
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:20,380
My duties that have been re-assigned to me, I will do my best to fulfill them here in Korea.

58
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:23,020
Please do, to the best of you capabilities then.

59
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,530
Oh, he's here.

60
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:26,740
Hi!

61
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:31,100
It's been a long time!
- Thank you for coming here.

62
00:06:31,780 --> 00:06:33,670
We are really honored to see you here.

63
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:40,020
We would like to make a proposal, since we need Miss Oh's ability this time.

64
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:44,150
Quick delivery and the guarantee of genuine products

65
00:06:44,150 --> 00:06:48,860
is the key to success of the reinforcement strategy project.

66
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:53,060
That's why we are suggesting it to you, Oh Ha Na.

67
00:06:56,040 --> 00:07:01,920
Cabin service staff should make the convenience and comfort of their passengers

68
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:10,480
their top priority in their work, as those responsible for their safety and comfort.

69
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:13,990
Please get up.

70
00:07:15,690 --> 00:07:18,090
- Hello!
- Hello!

71
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:20,540
Smile, say hello.

72
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,630
Yes.

73
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,310
We are finished.

74
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:36,200
Today, we're going to gather our friends together and have a dinner party. Do you want to come?

75
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:41,800
No. I have a scheduled video with my girlfriend in Korea.

76
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,560
A long-distance relationship? I can't do that.

77
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:50,220
I will be with her until the end, so it doesn't matter to me.

78
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:57,010
Mr. Choi Won, your service training was the best.

79
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:01,150
The people getting trained are very satisfied, that's why...

80
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:31,410
You must be tired. It's early morning there, right?

81
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:33,970
I waited to talk to you.

82
00:08:33,970 --> 00:08:36,220
That's why I came running back home after my work.

83
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:38,490
You must be hungry.

84
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:40,660
Tadah! I have it ready.

85
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:44,220
You have to eat properly though. What about those I sent you?

86
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:48,860
Yes, here...

87
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:51,570
I am eating them regularly.

88
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:55,070
Today at the office  something happened that made me happy.

89
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:56,010
What was that?

90
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:58,140
Even if I declined the transfer,

91
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:01,840
Jumei came to look for me. They want to work with me again.

92
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:04,570
Oh Ha Na is exceptional as expected.

93
00:09:04,570 --> 00:09:09,780
Today, I was complimented for my service training lecture, and so I received a proposal to extend my work here.

94
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:11,250
So?

95
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:13,320
I said I would have to think about it.

96
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,110
What? You'll think about it?

97
00:09:15,110 --> 00:09:17,840
Hey! Then are you saying you'll stay longer in Paris?

98
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,660
No, I  haven't decided yet.

99
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:24,520
- Are you mad?
- No.

100
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,740
You are angry, all right.

101
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:30,170
Okay, I will come back as soon as possible.

102
00:09:34,090 --> 00:09:35,720
You must be tired, right?

103
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:37,150
A little.

104
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,100
Sleep early tonight.

105
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,800
I think I should.

106
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:45,660
I had meetings all day long. And then I was waiting for your call.

107
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:47,920
I lack sleep.

108
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:50,380
I will wake you up four hours later.

109
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:53,530
I want to talk more.

110
00:09:57,190 --> 00:09:58,950
Ha Na.

111
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:00,580
Yeah.

112
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:04,760
Ha Na.

113
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:27,600
I love you.

114
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,930
Are you having indigestion?

115
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:55,140
But I only ate an apple today. It's strange.

116
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:57,710
Do you want to at least take some digestive medicine?

117
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:02,270
Thank you.

118
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:05,640
- Oh, the smell.
- Huh?

119
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:08,360
The water smells fishy.

120
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:13,330
It seems fine to me though. It doesn't smell like anything.

121
00:11:13,330 --> 00:11:16,690
Sunbaenim, will you please check this?

122
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,850
So Eun, thank you.

123
00:11:18,850 --> 00:11:23,510
- Oh, that's not it...
- Omo, Honey! Did you color your hair?

124
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:26,390
Yes! I went to Cheondamdong last week.

125
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:30,030
That exceptional keenness! I really have no one aside from our Purser!

126
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:35,070
The smell! You should have gotten a good one!

127
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,710
Aw, the smell!

128
00:11:36,710 --> 00:11:41,490
But this is expensive! It is not the cheap―

129
00:11:41,490 --> 00:11:46,630
Should I call that the mystery of aging? It's upgrading every time.

130
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:51,910
During the staff check a while ago, she was asking if someone sprayed perfume. It was big trouble!

131
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:56,970
She should date as soon as possible, or Sunbae Won should return right now. That's our only way to survive.

132
00:11:56,970 --> 00:11:58,650
Aigoo, seriously.

133
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:03,220
- Is she pregnant.
- Yeah, right, pregnant.  Huh?

134
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:06,370
So Eun, how could you think ...?

135
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:08,750
That can't be!

136
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:10,660
- Pregnant?
- Right?

137
00:12:10,660 --> 00:12:13,930
- Ah, seriously.
- Jeez.

138
00:12:27,090 --> 00:12:29,050
Team Leader.

139
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:35,330
Is something wrong?

140
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:39,970
Umm, Team leader ... umm

141
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:45,080
Did something happen to Dae Bok?

142
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:48,370
Our Dae Bok?

143
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:50,910
Why are you worried about him?

144
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:56,100
I can't contact him. Even when I call, he doesn't answer.

145
00:12:57,350 --> 00:12:59,000
What does this mean?

146
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:03,400
Are you two ... dating?

147
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:08,970
Yes ... I miss him, Team Leader.

148
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:29,240
Eun Jung

149
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:56,340
The number you are trying to call is not available for a video call. Do you want to do a voice call?

150
00:14:24,210 --> 00:14:28,290
♬ I couldn't say no ♬

151
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:34,190
♬ The more you ask the more I love ♬

152
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:40,260
Won, I suddenly thought of the history of our hideout.
♬ Even without any excuse ♬

153
00:14:42,070 --> 00:14:47,590
♬ I can only stand and turn around ♬

154
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:54,540
♬ Please don't blame me ♬

155
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:56,750
- Follow me.
- Where are you going ?

156
00:14:56,750 --> 00:15:00,690
♬ I will say what needs to be said ♬

157
00:15:00,690 --> 00:15:02,120
Cry here.

158
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:05,320
♬ Walking while crossing paths like this ♬

159
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:07,030
Where is this place?

160
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:11,810
A place where you can cry your heart out.
♬ is a long and endless journey ♬

161
00:15:11,810 --> 00:15:13,830
I looked for a place like this for a long time.

162
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:17,110
Scream.

163
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:21,560
A crying Choi Won who shut himself inside his room is really an eyesore.
♬ I'm heading toward you ♬

164
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:22,760
What are you doing?

165
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:27,850
Not inside a dark room, but in a place where you can look at the sky.
♬ We will always be the same ♬

166
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:34,170
Take in outside air as well.

167
00:15:34,170 --> 00:15:38,930
A place where you can let out your gloomy and upset feelings.

168
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:44,710
And also, the worried me.

169
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:47,130
A place that only we can go in.

170
00:15:48,370 --> 00:15:53,030
Isn't it great?

171
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,470
Good, isn't it?

172
00:15:54,470 --> 00:16:01,190
This place, other than a house, where you can cry to your heart's content, became our hideout.

173
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:09,040
When your mom left, it's the place that comforted your loneliness.

174
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:14,000
When you left for Santiago,

175
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:19,980
it's also here where I sometimes spent time with myself.

176
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:26,420
It is in this place that I realized how deeply rooted you are for me,

177
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:32,180
and where I realized my stupidity that  I didn't know about it for the longest time.

178
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:42,380
I want to see you, Choi Won.

179
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:46,020
Even if you aren't sad,

180
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:50,840
shedding tears when you miss someone

181
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:53,810
is what I came to know about because of you.

182
00:17:02,260 --> 00:17:05,650
Won Calling ********

183
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:23,760
Out of contact for several days ...

184
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,670
I'm worried.

185
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:29,910
What should I do?

186
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:32,900
- Unni.
- Oh!

187
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:37,740
Didn't you have any contact with Won?

188
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,990
I haven't.

189
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:43,750
Unni.  But, what's wrong with your face?

190
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:50,290
- Why? What?
- You seem to have lost a lot of weight. You look like a sick person.

191
00:17:50,290 --> 00:17:52,600
Did I already change that much?

192
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:56,380
What am I going to do, Ha Na?

193
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:07,950
You will talk about this with Teacher, right?

194
00:18:07,950 --> 00:18:12,020
Of course. It's not something I have to decide upon by myself.

195
00:18:12,810 --> 00:18:15,370
Are you intending to get married ... ?

196
00:18:15,370 --> 00:18:18,170
I don't know yet.

197
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:22,280
But, an old woman past forty

198
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:26,310
is not afraid of failure. I will, though my body will be the living evidence of that.

199
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:33,360
The truth that even if one is past forty years of age, she is still a woman, and so giving birth and being loved is still possible.

200
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,070
It is possible... right?

201
00:18:35,070 --> 00:18:36,890
Of course, Unni!

202
00:18:36,890 --> 00:18:41,700
I was worried and depressed because being forty is old and all that,

203
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:44,890
but seeing you, Unni, I thought I have to work harder.

204
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:48,700
I was being less zealous. That's what I think.

205
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:51,740
Would you console me?

206
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:56,220
Don't worry, huh? Everything's going to work out.

207
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:58,320
I also need words of blessing.

208
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:03,340
That child will bring you good fortune.

209
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:05,650
Thanks.

210
00:19:07,130 --> 00:19:09,550
I am going to tear up now.

211
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:11,570
Are you okay?

212
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:17,030
But, why did you come over?  Ah ... Won?

213
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:22,070
Yes.  Won hasn't contacted me for several days.

214
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:24,480
Won is really something.

215
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:27,220
He thought of going to Paris just to follow you there.

216
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:32,930
Love is really strange. It's immature and silly.

217
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:36,400
So, what about you? What's up with you and Won?

218
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:44,380
I'll tell you my secret too in return for you telling me yours.

219
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:52,070
Actually, Won and I are dating.

220
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:59,180
What? You two, really! Congratulations, really!

221
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:04,090
- But, we are really being careful.
- Why?

222
00:20:04,090 --> 00:20:08,590
We have been friends so long, but  if we stop being lovers

223
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:12,870
then what will we be?  What if we lose a friend?

224
00:20:12,870 --> 00:20:17,680
Won, both as a man and a friend, is so important to me.

225
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:20,850
If I think about losing one of them,

226
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:23,350
- I can't take it.
- Hey.

227
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:26,270
You should date him passionately first, and then worry about those things.

228
00:20:26,270 --> 00:20:29,170
Stop worrying, and just go for it.

229
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:31,930
I support the two of you.

230
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:35,210
Won must be really happy.

231
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:38,770
But that punk did not tell me anything! That kid!

232
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:42,230
Unni.

233
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:56,220
Ha Na.

234
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:08,030
I am even hearing things now.

235
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:10,230
Oh Ha Na.

236
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:15,540
No matter how much I miss him, I did not have this symptom though.

237
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:17,250
Please!

238
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:21,070
Oh Ha Na.

239
00:21:24,890 --> 00:21:27,400
I'm here! You are going to greet me, right?

240
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,630
Hey!

241
00:21:31,730 --> 00:21:35,800
You should have told me you were coming! I couldn't get a hold of you for days! Do you know how worried I was?

242
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:41,410
Ouch! I was going to surprise you. But I came! I couldn't take it any more because I missed you so much.

243
00:21:41,410 --> 00:21:45,310
Then why were you calling my name while hiding? You should have stood right before me.

244
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:49,330
- Are you angry? I was in the wrong.
- You did wrong, didn't you?

245
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:52,880
We finally meet after two months, so welcome me!

246
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:02,940
Ah, I think I'm finally back in Korea! This is really great!

247
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:04,860
Won, you're back?

248
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,670
You are not sick, are you?

249
00:22:10,150 --> 00:22:12,070
No. Father.

250
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:18,490
What's wrong with the two of you? You act like two secret lovers getting caught.

251
00:22:19,650 --> 00:22:22,740
You must have been eating foreign food, so come inside and eat with us.

252
00:22:22,740 --> 00:22:25,690
I'll tell Ha Na's mom.

253
00:22:25,690 --> 00:22:27,700
Yes.

254
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:37,400
Why are you so surprised? You quickly got on your feet. I feel hurt.

255
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,330
But you took your hands off first, Honey.

256
00:22:40,330 --> 00:22:43,260
Honey? Honey.

257
00:22:43,260 --> 00:22:45,130
You have to call me that from now on.

258
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:48,630
Because of that, I'm bearing with the hurt.

259
00:22:48,630 --> 00:22:50,380
So childish.

260
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:52,330
Honey.

261
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:54,560
Ugh, disgusting!

262
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,390
Honey!

263
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:00,350
I'm over here.

264
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:15,520
Oh Ha Na

265
00:23:31,150 --> 00:23:32,200
Yeah.

266
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:34,290
It's been a day.

267
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:36,750
Huh?

268
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:39,850
It's has been over 24 hours.

269
00:23:39,850 --> 00:23:43,120
I thought you must be tired, so I purposely didn't wake you up.

270
00:23:43,670 --> 00:23:46,910
I slept that long, huh.

271
00:23:46,910 --> 00:23:50,850
I'm about to get off work. I'll buy late-night snacks.

272
00:23:59,970 --> 00:24:06,540
I have never thought of giving birth and becoming a mother.

273
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:13,090
There are a lot of things I am afraid of, and I don't like being responsible for somebody else.

274
00:24:13,090 --> 00:24:18,480
My skin and body will be ruined, and I would have to be off work as well.

275
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:24,570
But I will give birth to this child.

276
00:24:24,570 --> 00:24:28,150
I can recover my skin and body if I work hard at it for a year.

277
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:31,210
I can go back to work after giving birth.

278
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:39,400
You should say something.

279
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:46,270
You already have your plans planned out, so why are you worried? You have to give birth to the child.

280
00:24:48,250 --> 00:24:51,410
Tell me in advance if you're going to the hospital. Don't go on your own.

281
00:24:51,410 --> 00:24:54,810
Do you mean you like it, or there's nothing you can do about it now?

282
00:24:56,610 --> 00:24:59,080
We would need to look for a house first.

283
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:01,240
Try to think of where would it be nice.

284
00:25:01,860 --> 00:25:03,430
House?

285
00:25:07,150 --> 00:25:09,050
Are you...

286
00:25:10,390 --> 00:25:12,760
proposing to me now?

287
00:25:17,230 --> 00:25:21,540
What kind of proposal is so out of the blue like that?

288
00:25:25,310 --> 00:25:27,820
Jong Hoon.

289
00:25:27,820 --> 00:25:35,420
♬  Oh, my life is changing every day ♬

290
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:39,190
♬  In every possible way ♬

291
00:25:41,650 --> 00:25:44,810
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

292
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:51,630
Hey, I'm not even surprised anymore. I knew they'd be like this.

293
00:25:51,630 --> 00:25:54,610
Did you?

294
00:25:54,610 --> 00:25:57,510
It has really turned out well!

295
00:25:57,510 --> 00:26:00,510
You really look good together.

296
00:26:00,510 --> 00:26:03,460
Hey, these are the fun times.

297
00:26:03,460 --> 00:26:07,830
Anyway, just ask me if there's something difficult. As your sunbae, who has been there, I can give you my know-how.

298
00:26:07,830 --> 00:26:10,400
Just take care of Jeong Mi.

299
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,310
Why aren't you saying anything?

300
00:26:12,310 --> 00:26:15,360
Hey, Oh Ha Na! It's because it's you that I'm giving up on Won.

301
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:20,780
I'm telling you this in advance. Since you started it, you should go until the end! Don't act out midway through, like these two!

302
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:23,690
I really hate losing my friends because you two break up.

303
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:26,530
Hey, Kang Na Yeong! Do you really have to say that now?

304
00:26:26,530 --> 00:26:30,160
Is this the first time in our house? Leave them alone.

305
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:32,290
- Drink!
- Drink!

306
00:26:32,290 --> 00:26:34,480
Hold up, hold up.

307
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:37,050
Haw far have you guys reached?

308
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:45,780
That's right! You're doing well!

309
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:49,770
I didn't do it, I didn't! Why do you all like it?

310
00:26:49,770 --> 00:26:52,370
- Thanks!
- Fighting.

311
00:26:52,370 --> 00:26:54,130
How about red ginseng?

312
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:56,480
Aria Airline Crew Personnel Schedule

313
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:02,650
Choi Won. Are you really alright?

314
00:27:02,650 --> 00:27:04,070
What about?

315
00:27:04,070 --> 00:27:06,270
Do you not know what the problem is now?

316
00:27:06,270 --> 00:27:09,420
Sunbaenim, was it really hard for you in France?

317
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:12,450
Me? It wasn't difficult at all.

318
00:27:19,010 --> 00:27:20,880
It was difficult.

319
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,880
It was hard.

320
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,200
It was extremely difficult.

321
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,540
Hey. Choi Won. Are you out of your mind?

322
00:27:30,650 --> 00:27:35,150
Is it only I who finds that kind of Sunbae Won strange? Awkward?

323
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:38,330
I'm really scared.

324
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:41,180
Sunbaenim, are you getting off work?

325
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:42,160
Yeah. You too?

326
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:46,060
Yes. Do you not feel hot?

327
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:50,070
It would be the best to have a glass of beer on this kind of day.

328
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:59,130
You drink beer with ice?

329
00:27:59,970 --> 00:28:02,550
This is how I beat the heat.

330
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:11,720
It's nice.

331
00:28:13,190 --> 00:28:17,330
- The training you've done in Paris, I heard you're doing it here.
- Yeah.

332
00:28:17,330 --> 00:28:19,200
I want to attend that training.

333
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:21,920
Alright. If you have the chance, do that.

334
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:23,150
Yes.

335
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:27,110
Ah, I heard things are going well for you and Unni Ha Na.

336
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:29,240
Yeah. Well.

337
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:35,100
I don't regret liking you.

338
00:28:35,100 --> 00:28:37,480
I will keep it as a good memory.

339
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:42,970
It's a relief I can comfortably call you Sunbaenim.

340
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:52,210
I find your feelings quite burdensome, but I learned from you that I need to express my feelings.

341
00:28:53,130 --> 00:28:54,670
Thanks.

342
00:28:55,730 --> 00:29:00,640
Sunbaenim, so is it because of me that your long one-sided love has come its end?

343
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:18,730
It's all done!

344
00:29:18,730 --> 00:29:22,780
All done! All done! All done!

345
00:29:25,060 --> 00:29:26,290
Give me food. I'm hungry.

346
00:29:26,290 --> 00:29:28,030
There's no food.

347
00:29:29,070 --> 00:29:30,880
Do you want to eat this instead?

348
00:29:33,190 --> 00:29:35,620
This will be a huge hit.

349
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:40,930
You are my son, but I really don't know.

350
00:29:44,990 --> 00:29:49,630
Go take a bath, please. You're so dirty.

351
00:29:58,370 --> 00:29:59,900
Jin In Nursing Home
#167 Neulno Village, Papyeong-myeon, Paju City, Gyeonggi Province

352
00:30:03,110 --> 00:30:04,130
What's this?

353
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:07,900
When you were in Paris, there was call about your mother.

354
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:09,950
He said she's here.

355
00:30:09,950 --> 00:30:14,870
It was quiet all this time, since there was no news of her. What's with a nursing home now?

356
00:30:18,220 --> 00:30:25,710
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

357
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:30,660
Should we stay here a little longer before going in?

358
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:34,350
Yes.

359
00:30:38,300 --> 00:30:40,390
I'm sorry.

360
00:30:40,390 --> 00:30:44,410
What are you sorry for? She said she wanted us to come together.

361
00:30:56,940 --> 00:30:58,770
Won.

362
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:01,570
Mom.

363
00:31:08,030 --> 00:31:11,650
He's been the one who has been taking care of me.

364
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:18,040
He's not my style, is he?

365
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,010
Yeah.

366
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:23,350
I'm sorry.

367
00:31:27,670 --> 00:31:32,440
If you were sick, why didn't you tell me when you called me that time?

368
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:36,200
I couldn't tell you. I feel sorry.

369
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:41,510
I am a bad mother who left her son all alone.

370
00:31:44,170 --> 00:31:47,640
Ha Na? Oh Ha Na?

371
00:31:48,370 --> 00:31:52,040
Yes. So you remember me.

372
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:57,090
I knew you'd be by Won's side.

373
00:31:58,570 --> 00:32:04,750
- Did you?
- It would be nice if you'd stay with him in the future as well.

374
00:32:05,950 --> 00:32:07,650
I will.

375
00:32:07,650 --> 00:32:13,210
You know Won more than me.

376
00:32:13,210 --> 00:32:15,400
I'm sure of it.

377
00:32:16,050 --> 00:32:19,460
Like someone with a young heart,

378
00:32:19,460 --> 00:32:24,800
I foolishly lived with the thought that it would not work if it wasn't love.

379
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:31,060
If I hadn't met this person, how would the latter part of my life turned out?

380
00:32:31,060 --> 00:32:34,630
He's an ordinary person, but to meet such a deep-hearted man

381
00:32:34,630 --> 00:32:39,810
and to pass with that person is something I'm grateful about.

382
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:43,640
Pass, what pass? You are still lively.

383
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:49,850
I have no confidence to meet you in my last moments.

384
00:32:49,850 --> 00:32:57,010
I called you because I wanted to have a talk with you while smiling.

385
00:33:00,870 --> 00:33:02,290
You did well.

386
00:33:02,290 --> 00:33:08,410
Even if I die, I don't need a funeral.

387
00:33:08,410 --> 00:33:12,860
Just, quietly, as if I'm here or not.

388
00:33:12,860 --> 00:33:14,920
Just like that.

389
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:22,320
Please do that for me, just as I wasn't there for you.

390
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,420
Was there ever a time you didn't do as you wished?

391
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:38,840
Don't worry. I'll come by often.

392
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:45,720
I'm sorry, but still

393
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:50,430
I loved you in my own way, son.

394
00:33:53,330 --> 00:33:54,710
Yeah.

395
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:02,660
It's a relief to have seen you.

396
00:34:04,330 --> 00:34:07,610
Thank you for coming.

397
00:34:22,580 --> 00:34:28,100
She said she didn't want to be a burden on her son so I only contacted you now,

398
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:32,710
although because of that, I was able to love her a lot.

399
00:34:32,710 --> 00:34:37,380
Thank you. I will come here when I have the time.

400
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:48,240
I think he really loves your mother.

401
00:34:50,140 --> 00:34:56,020
When Father passed away, Mother said she'd look for a person to love because she missed my father too much.

402
00:34:56,020 --> 00:34:58,580
I couldn't understand it then.

403
00:34:58,580 --> 00:35:02,070
But now, I realize

404
00:35:02,070 --> 00:35:05,470
she must have wanted to receive love.

405
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:11,520
What kind of person would Mother like?

406
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:14,180
Someone who is the complete opposite of that ahjusshi?

407
00:35:16,140 --> 00:35:17,980
But as you live,

408
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:20,400
I don't think you need those kinds of things.

409
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:23,680
That's right.

410
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:27,380
By the way. Didn't you say you have an ideal type?

411
00:35:27,380 --> 00:35:32,200
You said you'd find him through a kiss? Am I your ideal type or not?

412
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:36,570
Back in high school, do you remember our first kiss?

413
00:35:37,710 --> 00:35:39,280
I remember.

414
00:35:40,060 --> 00:35:42,800
I confirmed it back then.

415
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:55,600
What is it?

416
00:35:57,540 --> 00:35:59,980
You don't need to know.

417
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:02,880
Don't you think I need to know?

418
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:07,840
By chance, after kissing me, you thought, "This person isn't it"?

419
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:10,320
That's why you don't even say I love you?

420
00:36:26,930 --> 00:36:28,900
Yes, Eun Jung.

421
00:36:30,650 --> 00:36:34,580
I already told you a while ago, but I'm really not coming out.

422
00:36:34,580 --> 00:36:36,800
Please go back.

423
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:42,360
I'm really angry. Go!

424
00:36:57,300 --> 00:37:00,120
What is this?

425
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:02,920
What's the Hanja for this?

426
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:06,010
Flower? Flower 'hwa'.

427
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:10,670
Roll this.

428
00:37:15,460 --> 00:37:18,510
Please don't be angry anymore, Eun Jung.

429
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:20,900
I missed you.

430
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:31,840
I'm sorry.

431
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:39,600
Wow! I feel better!

432
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:44,400
This is a place I always pass by whenever I feel frustrated and drive around by myself.

433
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:46,460
I wanted to come here with you.

434
00:37:46,460 --> 00:37:49,700
You did well.

435
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:51,340
Let us...

436
00:37:52,510 --> 00:37:54,560
walk.

437
00:37:54,560 --> 00:37:57,800
- Should we?
- Wait.

438
00:37:57,800 --> 00:37:59,620
Done.

439
00:37:59,620 --> 00:38:01,970
Wow!

440
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:07,080
Let us

441
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:13,100
sometimes go on dates where we step on grass or step on sand.

442
00:38:13,100 --> 00:38:14,380
Okay.

443
00:38:14,380 --> 00:38:16,820
Should we take a couple picture?

444
00:38:16,820 --> 00:38:18,720
Okay.

445
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,840
Why are you taking pictures of our feet?

446
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:34,740
Won, looking at it now, your big toe is really big!

447
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:37,250
- Really?
- It's no joke.

448
00:38:38,540 --> 00:38:40,650
Your feet too are really...

449
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:43,880
Your feet are really pretty.

450
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,280
Really?

451
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:53,500
We have been friends for too long, but there's still a lot we don't know about each other, right?

452
00:38:53,500 --> 00:38:57,620
I think I'll be very excited whenever I learn of something new.

453
00:38:57,620 --> 00:39:01,540
"Ah, Ha Na is like this too."

454
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:04,860
"Wow, so fascinating. It's really nice!"

455
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:08,330
- Like this?
- Really?

456
00:39:08,330 --> 00:39:10,020
Won't you be disappointed?

457
00:39:10,020 --> 00:39:12,760
- Do you think you will?
- No.

458
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:14,820
See.

459
00:39:16,630 --> 00:39:18,180
Let's see.

460
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:22,920
They're looking.

461
00:39:24,120 --> 00:39:25,760
The best!

462
00:39:30,570 --> 00:39:33,110
What's up with the mood between the two of you today?

463
00:39:33,110 --> 00:39:34,900
It's somewhat different.

464
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:36,650
Really?

465
00:39:36,650 --> 00:39:39,300
- What's different?
- I'm not sure.

466
00:39:39,300 --> 00:39:42,820
How should I say it? Something's changed.

467
00:39:42,820 --> 00:39:46,580
Oh, you're really full of sense.

468
00:39:52,580 --> 00:39:56,720
- Alright. Look forward to today's special service.
- Okay!

469
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:02,120
But Ha Na.

470
00:40:02,120 --> 00:40:07,200
While we are apart, we called and texted each other a lot, didn't we?

471
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:09,780
- Yeah.
- But why

472
00:40:09,780 --> 00:40:13,750
haven't you told me you love me or sent me a heart or something?

473
00:40:13,750 --> 00:40:16,710
That's embarrassing, considering our relationship.

474
00:40:16,710 --> 00:40:20,210
Doesn't that kind of thing pop out no matter how much you want to hide it?

475
00:40:20,210 --> 00:40:24,480
- I told you I like you.
- But that's completely different!

476
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:29,880
Are you doing this on purpose because I told you I will never love you?

477
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:33,780
You... Did you meet another woman during one of your flights?

478
00:40:33,780 --> 00:40:38,840
- What nonsense are you talking about?
- Why are you uselessly arguing with me?

479
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:46,730
Speaking of which, you overdid your lipstick today. It's too sexy!

480
00:40:46,730 --> 00:40:49,900
This won't do. You use only that lipstick I chose yesterday.

481
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:51,510
No! Why should I?

482
00:40:51,510 --> 00:40:56,080
Hey,  do you know that the lipstick you use for the day depends on that day's outfit and mood?

483
00:40:56,080 --> 00:40:59,250
Hey, you should also factor in my feelings! My feelings!

484
00:41:05,490 --> 00:41:10,030
You, are you being sheepish and upset over something really ridiculous?

485
00:41:10,030 --> 00:41:12,420
Whatever.

486
00:41:12,420 --> 00:41:16,360
You get pissed so easily, and then you complain.

487
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:18,440
Why? I can't do that?

488
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:21,320
- You. Just stay right there.
- Why? What?

489
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:24,680
- I will ask my friend.
- Friend who?

490
00:41:31,450 --> 00:41:33,450
Oh Ha Na

491
00:41:38,380 --> 00:41:40,200
Hello?

492
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:45,100
I told you I am dating someone new, haven't I?

493
00:41:45,100 --> 00:41:48,560
Yeah. I heard he's a really good man.

494
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:52,620
What do I do now? He keeps grumbling and picking arguments during our date.

495
00:41:52,620 --> 00:41:58,980
That... I think he's only asking you to open up to him more.

496
00:41:58,980 --> 00:42:02,580
He can smoothly convince me and create the mood though.

497
00:42:02,580 --> 00:42:05,000
He must like you more than you like him.

498
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:09,760
Usually, the person who likes more is the one who is clumsy and makes mistakes.

499
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:15,020
How can you be sure? That he likes me more than I like him?

500
00:42:17,780 --> 00:42:20,920
Sometimes, I...

501
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:23,440
miss you, friend.

502
00:42:27,290 --> 00:42:29,890
Should we go back to being friends?

503
00:42:32,380 --> 00:42:33,910
No.

504
00:42:43,780 --> 00:42:48,200
I can sometimes take out my feelings for my boyfriend on you, right?

505
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:53,290
Of course! I am on your side.

506
00:42:53,290 --> 00:42:55,670
If he makes you upset, tell me. I'll go beat him up.

507
00:42:55,670 --> 00:43:00,510
You can't! I will handle my man preciously!

508
00:43:00,510 --> 00:43:03,380
I sometimes like being handled roughly.

509
00:43:03,380 --> 00:43:05,720
Really?

510
